<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP20_AdventureAwaits_ImaginaryFriend" s="481645">
  <T n="category">481599<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_AdventureAwaits--></T>
  <T n="name">0x2E93BAFF<!--String: "Imaginary Friends"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_ImaginaryFriend_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b24135233d4eee66</T>
      <T n="text">0x4C9DF011<!--String: "If your Child Sim is feeling a bit lonely and in need of a friend, head to Build Mode and purchase an <font color="#199C2C"><b>ImagineMe!</b></font> Doll, any of the four that speaks to them the most! Once purchased, your Sim can rename, play with, and start to befriend the doll! Be sure to <font color="#199C2C"><b>Change the Personality</b></font> of the doll now, before those choices become permanent upon turning the doll into an Imaginary Friend."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_ImaginaryFriend_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b24135233d4eee65</T>
      <T n="text">0x3691EC32<!--String: "Child Sims can turn their ImagineMe! Doll into a full-fledged Imaginary Friend if they satisfy at least one of these conditions: either reaching Level 3 Creativity Skill, Befriending the doll itself, or Neglecting their Social Need until they feel lonely enough to need an Imaginary Friend.\n\nOnce the doll has been turned into an Imaginary Friend, <font color="#199C2C"><b>the chosen personality and name are locked in</b></font>, so make sure you're absolutely ready before committing to spawning a new friend!\n\nEach doll can only be turned into an Imaginary Friend once (unless its owner dies), and each Sim can have one Imaginary Friend at a time.\nIf a child Sim who owns an Imaginary Friend changes households, they must keep their ImagineMe! Doll in their inventory before moving to preserve their original Imaginary Friend!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_ImaginaryFriend_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b24135233d4eee64</T>
      <T n="text">0x69FD514F<!--String: "Now that your Sim has an Imaginary Friend, they can be called in to keep your Sim company whenever they want! Imaginary Friends can do pretty much anything a normal Child can do, but keep in mind that they're only visible to the Sim that imagined them. Imaginary Friends will recommend different activities to do, and generally behave very differently, based on their personality. Evil Imaginary Friends might even offer the chance for your Sim to become just as Evil as them, if they wish!\n\nYour Sim can also temporarily <font color="#199C2C"><b>Send their Imaginary Friend back to Imaginary Land</b></font> when they want a break. Beyond that, if they never want to see their Imaginary Friend again, they can <font color="#199C2C"><b>Say Goodbye Forever</b></font>. But be warned, this is an irreversible decision!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_ImaginaryFriend_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b24135233d4eee63</T>
      <T n="text">0xAF369492<!--String: "But what if your Child Sim can't get enough of their Imaginary Friend? Once they've grown up to a Teen, assuming they've kept the ImagineMe! Doll around and maintained a good relationship with their Imaginary Friend, they can select the doll and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Offer to Make their Imaginary Friend Real</b></font>. This will allow the Imaginary Friend to join the household as a <font color="#199C2C"><b>real Sim</b></font>. The power to create life from your Sim's mind is in your hands!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_EP20_AdventureAwaits</E>
  </L>
